        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "17. As for us—This translation forms the best antithesis to the language of the heathen (La 4:15, 16). Calvin translates, \"While as yet we stood as a state, our eyes failed,\" &c.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "watched for a nation that could not save us—Egypt (2Ki 24:7; Isa 30:7; Jer 37:5-11).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Tzaddi.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
